        <abstract> 
<p>Interested in ACR’s Presidential Address [<hi rend="italic">Q. J. Geol. Soc. Lond.</hi> 19 (1863): xxix–lii] on the breaks in succession (of formations). Hopes ACR will provide a diagram of breaks, with the percentage of fossils that "pass upwards", i.e., continue to appear.</p> 
            <p>Horrified at Huxley’s geology.</p>
            <p>Wishes ACR would discuss "creeps".</p>
        </abstract>
